hopobject.body: The National Gallery moulindelaville.com Does patenting DNA – specifically isolated human DNA – spur innovation, improve health and contribute to a better future? Thirty years of medical biotechnology breakthroughs support a strongly affirmative "yes." But you wouldn't know it if you've been following the debate about patenting human genes in a lawsuit sponsored by the American Civil Liberties Union against Myriad Genetics, Inc.
